Lirik:

Bagaimana nak ku luahkan rasa ini
Bagaimana nak ku ungkapkan rasa ini
Dicintaimu, mencintaimu setulus hati
Bagaimana bisa semu-wa sepantas ini

Segenap rasa dan segenap takdir
Kan semua nya dari Ilahi
Kan kita yang mohon di bukakan jalan, dibukakan hati
Usah diragukan segenap rasa,
Usah curiga segenap takdir
Kan yang memberi kan segenap rasa,
Yang Melakar takdir

Semoga di buka jalan dan hati

Tak kan kubiarkan redup
Dari berjuta detik yang pernah kita lewati

Aku tak mau berhenti untuk terus mencintamu
Kamu yang ada di doaku
Kamu yang selalu aku semogakan
Melekat erat ada di jantung hatiku

Ketika aku melihatmu
Aku jatuh di paling cinta

Terus doakanmu

Yuji Itadori is a boy with tremendous physical strength, though he lives a completely ordinary high school life. One day, to save a classmate who has been attacked by curses, he eats the finger of Ryomen Sukuna, taking the curse into his own soul. From then on, he shares one body with Ryomen Sukuna. Guided by the most powerful of sorcerers, Satoru Gojo, Itadori is admitted to Tokyo Jujutsu High School, an organization that fights the curses... and thus begins the heroic tale of a boy who became a curse to exorcise a curse, a life from which he could never turn back.

snippet.title: Marvel Animation's Marvel Zombies - Official Trailer #2 (2025) Elizabeth Olsen, Paul Rudd
snippet.description:
Check out the Trailer #2 for Marvel Animation’s Marvel Zombies, an animated horror installment to the Marvel Cinematic Universe distributed by Marvel Studios. This series re-contextualizes the Marvel Universe as Earth's mightiest heroes go head-to-head against a zombie outbreak, turning even the strongest of them into undead nightmares. Marvel Animation’s Marvel Zombies will be a four-part event on September 24, streaming exclusively on Disney+.

After the Avengers are overtaken by a zombie plague, a desperate group of survivors discover the key to bringing an end to the super-powered undead, racing across a dystopian landscape and risking life and limb to save their world. 
 
Marvel Zombies stars Elizabeth Olsen, Paul Rudd, Florence Pugh, David Harbour, Tessa Thompson, Simu Liu, Awkwafina, Hailee Steinfeld, Wyatt Russell, Randall Park, Iman Vellani, Dominique Thorne, and more. The series is executive produced by Kevin Feige, Louis D’Esposito, Brad Winderbaum, Dana Vasquez-Eberhardt, Bryan Andrews, and Zeb Wells, and is produced by Danielle Costa, Carrie Wassenaar. 

Marvel Animation’s Marvel Zombies will be a four-part event on September 24, streaming exclusively on Disney+.

#MarvelZombies #Marvel #IGN

snippet.title: DIOR大穎 - LOUISE - (Official MV）
snippet.description:
今天是我們認識的第三個月
I wrote a song for my friend👭



This is a simple story I’d like to share with all of you！

Back in June this year, when I wasn’t in the best place emotionally, I went to London to study. 
That’s where I met a classmate （LOUISE）
who unexpectedly became a very close friend.

We only spent three weeks together,
but it felt like fate — as if she was an angel sent to remind me
that the world is so much bigger, with so many things worth chasing.
So, I wrote this song to remember that time, 
to celebrate the moment I found clarity in myself, 
and to treasure every encounter that leads to the next meeting.

Because our English wasn’t great, that’s why we ended up in the same class in London HAHAHAH
We even promised to go to Australia next year for two more months of English lessons together, to keep growing into better versions of ourselves！

That’s also why this is the very first English song I’ve ever written 
I really using up all the vocabulary I know, haha.

Anyways! Thank you so much for listening to my music and my story.
My name is Dior, and I’m a singer-songwriter from Malaysia,Johor,Batu Pahat,Rengit. 
I’M A KAMPUNG GIRL!

I never imagined myself
stepping into the world of English songs.

But maybe… that’s what life is about.
You’ll never know where the road takes you
unless you keep moving forward.

So, whatever you’re going through,
let the wind carry you onward. ✨




《Louise》
作詞：DIOR大穎
作曲：DIOR大穎
演唱：DIOR大穎、LOUISE

I met an angel
Oh her name is Louise
She’s only just turned eighteen
Oh she’s still chasing her dream

It’s not easy to find a friendship like this
Even though we only had a few weeks
But it still means a lot to me

Ohh girl, you don’t know how much you healed me
You woke a part I couldn’t see
You never know
You never know
You let me be 

We said goodbye till we meet again
And said goodbye but it’s not the end
Said goodbye, remember us this way
Till the end
All the little things with you I won’t forget

Let me tell you a secret
We don’t care what you think
Maybe we got a little crazy
But life is still young
We‘re born to be free

Take it easy
Try to live it wild and free
Sometimes life - a little hazy
So maybe just let it be

Oh girl, you don’t know how much you healed me
You woke a part I couldn’t see
You never know
you never know
你讓我成為自己

We said goodbye till we meet again
And said goodbye but it’s not the end
Said goodbye, remember us this way
Till the end
All the little things with you I won’t forget

Goodbye till we meet again
And said goodbye but it’s not the end
Said goodbye, remember us this way
Till the end
All the little things with you I won’t forget

Let‘s say goodbye till we meet again
And say goodbye but it’s not the end
Say goodbye, remember us this way
Till the end
Day by day we stay the same
See you again

I would be your girl

혹시 우리가 서로를 잃어도

이제 알았어 그때 왜 그랬는지
반쯤 미쳐 너의 이름을 불렀는데

I can’t hear what you’re saying
돌아와 줘 내게 너도 미쳐있었던 내게
You’re breaking my heart
(I don’t know why you did this to me)

또다시 찾아오는 아침에 내가 없어도
안기며 웃던 날 기억 못 해도
아프긴 하지만 괜찮아 너니까
You know I’ll always be with you, baby

더 깊어져 가는 밤안개 속 그 길 위에서
혹시 우리가 서로를 또 잃어도
날 사랑했던 널 찾아갈 테니까
You know I’ll always be with you, baby

난 아프다
참 아프다
또 아프다
You know I’ll always be with you, baby

I’m falling apart
My love is gone
I’m breaking down

snippet.title: Thangapoovey - Video Song | Madharaasi | Sivakarthikeyan | Rukmini | A.R.Murugadoss | Anirudh
snippet.description:
Junglee Music Tamil presents the video song of “Thangapoovey” from the much-awaited film Madharaasi, written and directed by acclaimed filmmaker A.R. Murugadoss. Featuring the charismatic Sivakarthikeyan and the graceful Rukmini Vasanth in lead roles, this soulful track is composed by none other than Anirudh Ravichander, known for his chart-topping melodies and heart-touching compositions. Thangapoovey blends emotion with melody, capturing the essence of love and longing with poetic visuals and heartfelt lyrics.

With its mesmerizing tune and lyrical depth, Thangapoovey promises to strike a chord with music lovers and fans of Tamil cinema alike. Whether you're a follower of romantic Tamil songs or a die-hard fan of Anirudh’s music, this lyrical video is a must-watch. As anticipation builds for Madharaasi, this song sets the perfect tone, offering a glimpse into the film’s emotional landscape.
